OL,3,C'Losing my sight is the reason i'm
OL,4,Cclean and sober'
OL,6,F"But I remember waking up on the bed
OL,7,Fface down with a bottle of vodka in my
OL,8,Fhand and them times were often.
OL,10,F"I remember sitting at the end of the
OL,11,Fbed debating whether to take my own
OL,12,Flife because I couldn't deal with it
OL,13,Fanymore. I pushed everybody away."
OL,15,FBut through recovery meetings and a
OL,16,Fsponsor who gave him no excuses, Ray
OL,17,Ftransformed his sight loss into
OL,18,Fpurpose.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/5
